Definition of Done

The MVP is considered complete when a user can:

Launch the LabForge desktop application.
Configure a small business environment using the graphical interface.
Generate a valid YAML configuration.
Deploy the environment to a Hyper-V host.
Automatically provision a working Active Directory domain.
Automatically deploy and join two Windows clients.
Create users, groups, Organizational Units, and shared folders.
Produce a deployment report.
Successfully recover from deployment failures through rollback mechanisms where supported.
Vision Beyond Version 1.0

Version 1.0 establishes the deployment engine that future releases will build upon. Planned future capabilities include:

Additional virtualization providers (Proxmox, VMware, KVM/libvirt)
Security deployment profiles
Monitoring and health dashboards
Endpoint lifecycle management
Backup and disaster recovery
Enterprise policy management
Plugin architecture
Cybersecurity lab deployment templates
